cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for 3D object recognition. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new clustering and pooling layer based on dominant sets, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores a fast approximate learning strategy, which falls under the category of optimization and search algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the proposed method for robotics applications, which falls under the category of robotics and automation, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a recurrent neural network architecture, which falls under the category of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
